Tonight, the government has issued a 14-day ultimatum for the united nations high commissioner for refugees (UNHCR) to close down Dadaab and Kakuma refugee camps located in Kenya. in a brief statement posted on social media, the interior ministry asked UNHCR to provide a roadmap on the definite closure of the two camps that has hosted hundreds of thousands of refugees for many years. and as our senior reporter Duncan khaemba reports, the statement said there was no room for further negotiations.